The article is a transcript of remarks made by Vice President Mike Pence during a celebration of Hispanic Heritage Month at the Naval Observatory in Washington, D.C. Pence thanks the attendees, including Secretary of Labor Alex Acosta and Second Lady Karen Pence, and recognizes the contributions of Hispanic Americans to various sectors of American society. He also discusses the administration's commitment to strengthening ties with Latin American countries, efforts to support Puerto Rico in the aftermath of Hurricane Maria, and the importance of faith in the Hispanic community. Pence concludes by expressing his admiration for the Hispanic American community and his belief in a bright future for both the community and the United States.